Pattern- Visited Array/Cycle detection

Code-

var arrayNesting = function(nums) {
    let n = nums.length;
    let visited = new Array(n).fill(false);
    let maxLen = 0;

    for (let i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        if (!visited[i]) {
            let count = 0;
            let current = i;

            while (!visited[current]) {
                visited[current] = true;
                current = nums[current];
                count++;
            }

            maxLen = Math.max(maxLen, count);
        }
    }

    return maxLen;
};



Problem-
Given permutation array nums
Build set:
- nums[k] → nums[nums[k]] → ...
Stop when element repeats
Return maximum size of such set

Key Idea-
- Each index forms a cycle
- Traverse cycle and count length
- Mark visited to avoid recomputation

Steps-
Create visited array (size n, initialized false)
Initialize maxLen = 0
For each index i:
-If not visited:
  -Start from i
  -Traverse until visited:
   -mark visited
   -move to next = nums[current]
   -count length
-Update maxLen
